IT Manager is one of the most prestigious and therefore one of the most difficult competitions of Xactitude 2K15. It consists of four rounds, each designed to test a particular facet of a manager\'s ability to do one thing: handle stress. Starting off with an aptitude test that pitches brainpower against time, the participants move on to the group discussion and stress task rounds that tests their assertiveness and ability to get a job done. Finally, those that remain are interviewed in front of hundreds of people to judge their ability to think quickly, answer succinctly, and beat the best to become Xactitude\'s IT manager.

You do not truly know a subject until you can teach it to someone else. The Lecture Contest tests the participant\'s speaking ability as well as their knowledge of the subject. An audience favourite, as it brings future technology within the grasp of the possible.

The one IT event that gives preference to Information over Technology, IT Quiz tests the participants on a variety of IT trivia that will separate the good from the great. Those that survive the gruelling written preliminary round will be taken to the main stage, where a host of different rounds will test their speed, accuracy, and ability to think under pressure when presented with auditory and visual clues.

A cheeky play on words, promptitude is all about solving problems promptly from the command prompt, and proving to the world that solving complex problems by typing a few lines of code is not just an invention of Hollywood - it is a skill, honed to perfection by the very best.

An event that will start before the real battle begins. Team effort and dedication is the only key to success, in this exciting event. Stay together, Stay awake, Work together to accomplish the goals. Team of three will have to cross various hurdles throughout the event to reach the victory stand.

Testing your photoshopping skills at a professional level, Vicissitude takes the best morphers and Photoshop artists of India and pits them against time and each other. With only an hour to work in, there is no time for mistakes - only perfection.

In an era where coding literacy is almost as important as that of spoken languages, perfection can only be truly achieved when one\'s code is beautiful - both in its aesthetic qualities and in its simplicity. The Web Design Competition tests one\'s ability to use code to make a useful, intuitive and beautiful website in under an hour.

If physical agility and strength have taken a backseat in the IT industry, mental acuity and superfast reaction time have definitely reached a new level among the scores of gamers that populate the leading IT companies of India. Only practice and teamwork will give you the skills necessary to emerge victorious from this winner-take-all competition.

Our humble attempt at reversing the trend among IT professionals to abandon exercise and become sluggish. Desuetude takes the lost art of teamwork and exploration and combines it with quick wits to solve clues, eliminate possibilities and race towards treasure and glory. Don\'t be surprised to find yourself tapping long forgotten skills and thinking out of the box to solve some of the clues.
